&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR MANAGER, FORECASTING &amp;amp; ANALYTICS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;New York, San Francisco&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TL;DR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aura&#39;s Revenue Organization is building a world-class analytics function to drive forecast accuracy, smarter marketing investment, and growth across our retail and e-commerce channels. As Senior Manager of Revenue Forecasting &amp;amp; Analytics, you&#39;ll turn historical and real-time sell-through, marketing, and channel data into the demand forecasts and analytical insight that help the business put the right products in the right markets - and spend marketing dollars where they actually drive profitable demand. You&#39;ll work at the intersection of forecasting, marketing analytics, business intelligence, and cross-functional decision-making to build the revenue analytics function that supports Aura&#39;s growth across North America, Europe, and expanding international markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our story -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aura was founded by two early Twitter software engineers who wanted to take what they knew about social connections and create a way for families to come together around their best memories. The combination of seamless sharing across a smartphone app and a beautiful digital frame resonated, and Aura is now used by millions of families with more than 1 billion photos shared in 2025 alone. What is known as the best digital picture frame by Wirecutter has always been about something more ambitious: a private, trusted platform for connection with your close loved ones. Aura is now available in thousands of leading retail stores across North America and Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting directly to the CRO, you&#39;ll combine statistical forecasting, SQL-based business intelligence, and marketing analytics to improve forecast accuracy, connect marketing spend to demand, and enable data-driven decisions across the revenue org. This is an analyst role at heart: you&#39;ll live in the data, build the models and views the team relies on, and translate them into clear recommendations - not run a formal S&amp;amp;OP function. If you&#39;re energized by forecasting, marketing analytics, and turning messy data into decisions that move the business, this is a chance to make a meaningful contribution to Aura&#39;s continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Forecasting &amp;amp; Accuracy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain rolling revenue forecasts at the SKU / channel / geography level across Aura&#39;s portfolio, using SQL-based data and statistical methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refresh forecasts on a regular cadence and ahead of major launches, promotions, and peak periods, incorporating POS, sell-through, marketing performance, and inventory signals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track forecast accuracy (MAPE, bias, WAPE) at the SKU / channel / week grain, set internal accuracy targets, and continuously refine methodology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use statistical forecasting techniques to generate baselines and identify opportunities for model improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marketing &amp;amp; Channel Analytics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze channel-level acquisition economics (CPA/CAC, payback) and surface where spend is - and isn&#39;t - driving profitable demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quantify the demand impact of campaigns, promotions, and launches, and fold those signals into the forecast rather than treating them as noise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Marketing to pressure-test attribution and channel-mix assumptions against actual sell-through, and support incrementality / holdout testing where it matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the link between marketing spend, demand

